President Obama, the First Lady, Vice President Biden, and other government officials will participate in memorial events and community service projects in honor of Martin Luther King, Jr. Day. Led by the Corporation for National and Community Service and the King Center, the Day of Service encourages Americans to come together to meet the needs of their communities and commit to service throughout the year. The events will take place in Washington, D.C., Atlanta, Georgia, and other locations. Cabinet Secretaries and Administration officials will be participating in various events, including service projects, speeches, and meals for those in need. The Martin Luther King, Jr. National Day of Service will include thousands of projects across the country.